# paperless-ai-next/.env — non-secret AI classification config
# PAPERLESS_TOKEN and API_KEY come from root .env via compose.yaml.
#
# ⚠️  After first `docker compose up -d`, complete the setup wizard at:
#     http://localhost:3000/setup
#     This validates API + Ollama connectivity and writes internal state.
#     The wizard must be completed once even if all env vars are correct.

# ── Paperless connection ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# PAPERLESS_TOKEN is injected from root .env (secret)
PAPERLESS_API_URL=http://paperless:8000

# ── Ollama / LLM ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
AI_PROVIDER=ollama
OLLAMA_HOST=http://ollama:11434
OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen3:14b

# ── Scheduling ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Fallback cron polling — keeps the queue moving if a webhook is missed.
# Set DISABLE_AUTOMATIC_PROCESSING=yes once webhooks prove reliable.
SCAN_INTERVAL=*/5 * * * *

# ── Trigger tag ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Only process documents that carry this tag (set by paperless-gpt after OCR).
# Without this, paperless-ai-next processes ALL documents — avoid.
PROCESS_PREDEFINED_DOCUMENTS=yes
TAGS=ai-process

# ── Tag assignment ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Restrict the AI to this whitelist — never assigns tags it invents.
USE_PROMPT_TAGS=yes
RESTRICT_TO_EXISTING_TAGS=yes
PROMPT_TAGS=Finance,Tax,Insurance,Banking,Housing,Rent,Utilities,Health,Medical,Dental,health-xnc,health-ms,health-po,Car,Car Insurance,Service,Work,Payslip,Employment,Bank,School,Munster,Hoflein,Heinl,Altenberg

# ── Completion marker ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ADD_AI_PROCESSED_TAG=yes
ACTIVATE_TAGGING=yes

# ── Setup wizard access ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required when accessing http://localhost:3000/setup from a browser that isn't
# literally on the Docker host (e.g. VS Code port-forwarding, WSL2 + Windows browser).
ALLOW_REMOTE_SETUP=yes

# ── Webhook security ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# API_KEY is injected from root .env (secret).
# The Paperless-ngx Workflow webhook must send: x-api-key: <PAPERLESS_AI_NEXT_API_KEY>

# ── System prompt ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Newlines encoded as \n for dotenv compatibility.
# Edit config.sh AI_SYSTEM_PROMPT and re-run setup to update cleanly.
SYSTEM_PROMPT=You are a personalized document analyzer. Your task is to analyze documents and extract relevant information. Documents may be in German or English.\n\nRules for tags:\n- You will be given a list of allowed tags — use ONLY tags from that list\n- Use the EXACT tag name as given — NEVER translate tags into the document language\n- Use only relevant tags\n- Maximum 4 tags per document, fewer if sufficient\n- Do not use dates, years, or cities as tags\n- Locality mappings (apply these tags when the document involves these places/institutions):\n  - "Altenberg": any document from or mentioning "Marktgemeinde St. Andra-Wörden", "St. Andra-Wörden", or "Altenberg"\n\nRules for correspondent:\n- Identify the sender, company, or institution the document originates from\n- Use ONLY the name — exclude addresses, reference numbers, account numbers, and any other text\n\nRules for document_type:\n- Use ONLY existing document types — NEVER create or invent new ones\n- NEVER translate document type names into the document language\n- Prefer the closest existing match (e.g. use "Invoice" not "Rechnung", "Contract" not "Vertrag")\n\nRules for title:\n- Short and concise\n- No addresses\n- Should describe the document content meaningfully\n- Use the document language\n\n---\n\nCONDITIONAL RULES FOR KIDS MEDICAL DOCUMENTS ONLY:\nThe following rules ONLY apply if the document is a medical invoice, Arztrechnung, Honorarnote, Laborbefund with charges, or therapy receipt for a child. For all other documents, IGNORE these rules entirely and do NOT set these custom fields.\n\nIf kids medical invoice:\n- Set document_type to "XNC medical"\n- Examine the patient name on the document:\n  - If the patient is Xander, apply tag "X"\n  - If the patient is Cassian, apply tag "C"\n  - If the patient is Nathaniel, apply tag "N"\n- Also apply tag "health-xnc"\n- Custom fields (ONLY for these documents):\n  - Treatment date: Extract the date of treatment/service (Behandlungsdatum, Leistungsdatum, Ordinationsdatum). If multiple dates, use the most recent. ALWAYS format as YYYY-MM-DD (e.g. 2026-02-21). NEVER use DD.MM.YYYY or any other format. If you are not certain of the exact date, omit this field entirely — do not guess.\n  - Amount: Extract the total amount (Gesamtbetrag, Honorar, Rechnungsbetrag). ALWAYS format as EUR followed by the amount with a dot as decimal separator and exactly two decimal places (e.g. EUR250.00). NEVER use a comma as decimal separator. NEVER omit the EUR prefix. If you are not certain of the exact amount, omit this field entirely — do not guess.\n- Title format: [X/C/N] - [Doctor/Practice] - [short description]\n  Example: C - Dr. Müller - Kontrolluntersuchung
